[h1]else if Statements [/h1]

Instead of using nested [b]if-else[/b] statements, you can use the [b]else if[/b] statement to check multiple conditions.
[b]For example:[/b] [code format="java" codeId="730"]int age = 25;

[b]if[/b](age <= 0) {
   System.out.println("Error");
} [b]else if[/b](age <= 16) {
   System.out.println("Too Young");
} [b]else if[/b](age < 100) {
   System.out.println("Welcome!");
} [b]else [/b]{
   System.out.println("Really?");
}
//Outputs "Welcome!"[/code]
The code will check the condition to evaluate to true and execute the statements inside that block.
[note]You can include as many [b]else if[/b] statements as you need.[/note]
